@page "/Error"

@* Friendly error page shown in production when something goes wrong
   (wired up in Program.cs via UseExceptionHandler). *@

<h1 class="text-danger">Something went wrong</h1>
<p>An unexpected error occurred. Try going back to the <a href="/">project list</a>.</p>
<p class="text-muted">
    If this keeps happening, check the app logs:
    <code>docker compose logs -f app</code>
</p>
